In contrast to previous results we found no clear evidence of declines in synchrony in recent decades, during a period of significant warming \citep{Bogdziewicz2020, Foest2024}. Synchrony across trees within a population varied over time but has not clearly changed in recent periods (recent declines in 2015 onward are within the 90\% range of previous periods, Fig. \ref{fig:synchrony}). 
